  "title": "Technical Sales Consultant",
  "description": "<p>Leads business development and relationships to support pipeline building in partnership with our customers. Leverage relationships to bring distinctive insights and innovations to expand our opportunities.</p><p><strong>Essential Job Functions:</strong></p><p>• Contribute to the company's business advisory and development strategy and ensure alignment with organizational goals.</p><p>• Manage a team of business development professionals, offering guidance and support to drive success.</p><p>• Establish and maintain client relationships, working to understand evolving client needs and identify growth opportunities.</p><p>• Identify and pursue new business opportunities, collaborating with senior leadership to drive market expansion.</p><p>• Leverage market insights to bring distinctive ideas and innovations that expand business opportunities.</p><p>• Assist the sales and marketing teams in achieving their targets by providing strategic input.</p><p>• Continuously analyze market trends, competitor activities, and regulatory changes to inform strategic decisions.</p><p>• Contribute to revenue growth through effective sales and business development efforts, ensuring targets are met.</p><p><strong>Basic Qualifications:</strong></p><p>• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field or equivalent combination of education and experience</p><p>• Typically, 8+ years of relevant work experience in industry, with a minimum of 3+ years in a similar role</p><p>• Proven experience in driving business development and advisory initiatives</p><p>• Proficiencies in sales strategies, market analysis, and technology trends</p><p>• A continuous learner who stays abreast of industry knowledge and technology advancements</p><p><strong>Other Qualifications:</strong></p><p>• Advanced degree in a relevant field is a plus</p><p>• Relevant certifications (e.g., Sales Leadership, Sales Enablement, Business Development) are a plus</p>",
